Feature 5: Recurring & Follow-up Meetings (User-Friendly)

This feature allows users to create parent meetings with recurring sessions, track follow-up meetings, carry forward open tasks, and display them in a clear, user-friendly interface. The goal is to make it easy for users to focus on the current follow-up meeting while keeping previous follow-ups accessible but collapsed.

Epic 5.1: Recurring Meeting Setup

Enable users to schedule meetings that repeat regularly.

User Stories:

Parent Meeting Creation: As a user, I want to create a parent meeting (e.g., "Leads Meeting") so that recurring sessions are grouped under one title.

Set Recurrence: As a user, I want to set recurrence options (daily, weekly, bi-weekly, monthly) and select the day of the week so that meetings are automatically scheduled.

Ad-hoc Follow-ups: As a user, I want to schedule follow-up meetings on custom dates outside the regular recurrence so that special meetings can be added.

Epic 5.2: Follow-up Meeting Structure

Manage follow-up meetings under a parent meeting.

User Stories:

Inherit Parent Title: As a user, I want each follow-up meeting to inherit the parent meeting title so that all sessions are clearly grouped.

Individual Dates: As a user, I want follow-up meetings to have their own dates while staying linked to the parent meeting so that tasks are tracked per session.

Carry Forward Open Tasks: As a user, I want open agenda points from the previous follow-up to automatically appear in the new follow-up meeting so that unfinished work is not lost.

Epic 5.3: Agenda & Task Tracking Across Follow-ups

Track and manage agenda points for recurring meetings.

User Stories:

Add New Agenda Points: As a user, I want to add agenda points specific to a follow-up meeting so that each session contains relevant discussions.

Task Responsibility & Status: As a user, I want each agenda point to have a responsible person, status (open/closed), and optional notes so that accountability is clear.

Visual Indicators: As a user, I want a visual distinction for follow-up meetings and their agenda points so that it’s easy to identify the current follow-up and previous sessions.

Epic 5.4: User-Friendly Dashboard & Navigation for Follow-ups

Improve visibility and usability for recurring meetings.

User Stories:

Highlight Current Follow-up: As a user, I want the current follow-up meeting’s agenda points to be expanded and highlighted so that I can focus on what needs immediate attention.

Collapse Previous Follow-ups: As a user, I want previous follow-up meetings to be collapsed by default so that the interface is uncluttered and easy to read.

Quick Navigation Between Follow-ups: As a user, I want to expand/collapse any follow-up meeting and jump to it easily so that I can compare current and past tasks when needed.

Epic 5.5: Notifications & Reminders for Follow-ups

Ensure responsible members are reminded of open tasks across follow-ups.

User Stories:

Detect Open Tasks: As a user, I want the system to detect open tasks in follow-up meetings so that no task is missed.

Send WhatsApp Reminders: As a responsible person, I want to receive a WhatsApp reminder for my open tasks in the current follow-up meeting so that I complete them on time.

Contextual Reminder Messages: As a user, I want reminders to include the follow-up meeting title, date, and task description so that the recipient clearly understands what needs to be done.